üìå Branch and PR Protection ‚úÖ Codebase 100% compatible ‚Äî Implementation deferred by operational choice

All audit scripts, pipelines, and security tooling are fully compatible with strict branch protection rules (e.g., required reviews, status check enforcement, and up-to-date-with-main constraints). However, since development is currently handled directly by two developers only, we chose not to activate these rules, as real-time auditing is already enforced via the CI workflow YAML.

Protection can be enabled at any time with no changes needed in the codebase.

0.3.6 üì• Pull Request Evidence Requirements Each PR that modifies code must include:

‚úÖ Semgrep JSON Report: semgrep-.json

‚úÖ SonarCloud JSON Report: sonarcloud-.json

‚úÖ Source File(s): must include the standard audit header (see 0.3.3)

üîó SonarCloud Link: direct URL to analysis result

üñºÔ∏è Screenshot: passing Quality Gate (optional but recommended)

0.3.7 üîê File Integrity Verification To guarantee cryptographic integrity of audited files:

sh shasum -a 256 file_name.tsx > file_name.tsx.sha 0.3.8 ‚úÖ Compliance Outcome Once validated via audit header, hash verification, and CI artifacts, each source code file is:

