üß© Product Modules ‚Äî Description & Limitations Each module below follows auditable standards, focusing on compliance, traceability, and SaaS integration.

‚öì BTMaritime ‚Äì Maritime Compliance as a Service
Use case
Auditable sea routes (AIS + KMZ) with automatic validation against MARPOL, NORMAM and STCW ‚Äî 100 % SaaS, no onboard hardware.

1 ‚Ä¢ Stakeholder Pain Matrix
Stakeholder	Core Pain	Latent / Emergent Pain
Shipowner / Operator	Fines, embargoes and delays due to environmental non-compliance	No immutable evidence for ESG due diligence
ESG Manager	Investor pressure for verifiable metrics	Low-granularity data for annual reports
Compliance / Legal	Hard to prove retroactive compliance	Reputational risk in pollution incidents
2 ‚Ä¢ Key Features (MVP v1.0)
Geolocation rule engine ‚Äî real-time route validation vs. MARPOL / NORMAM / STCW
Checklist-as-code ‚Äî auto-generation of ‚Äúbefore-sail‚Äù and ‚Äúafter-arrival‚Äù checklists per voyage
Blockchain + QR certification ‚Äî SHA-256 hash, UTC timestamp and QR for offline port inspection
Legal radar & audit log ‚Äî incident panel, response SLA, SOC 2-proof trail
3 ‚Ä¢ Competitive Edge (Four Actions)
Create	Eliminate	Reduce	Raise
Geolocated validation + on-chain certificates	Manual processes & dedicated hardware	Ramp-up & learning curve	Auditability, API integration, non-compliance feedback
4 ‚Ä¢ Compliance Coverage
Framework	Control Mapping
IMO MARPOL / ISPS	Reg. 73/78 Annexes I-VI
ISO 14001 / 27001	A.12, A.15, A.18 (logging, supplier risk)
SOC 2	Security, Availability, Processing Integrity
ESG	Scope 3 disclosures (blockchain-verifiable)
5 ‚Ä¢ Technical Architecture (High-Level)
1 -Edge Collector ‚Äî ingests AIS / ADS-B, normalises & encrypts (AES-256)

2 -Rule Engine (OPA) ‚Äî evaluates MARPOL / NORMAM policies in WebAssembly

3 -Event Stream (Kafka) ‚Äî publishes compliance events in JSON Schema

4 -Certifier Service ‚Äî hashes, signs (ECDSA) and stores on public Polygon chain

5 -Dashboard / API ‚Äî Grafana + REST / GraphQL, CSV / XBRL export for ESG partners

6 -Tenant Isolation & Data Governance ‚Äî all sensitive customer data is logically isolated per tenant using backend-enforced multi-tenancy controls. This design ensures full compliance with LGPD and other international privacy standards. User authentication, data access, and audit logs are segregated and validated per tenant scope, supporting secure RegTech infrastructure.
6 ‚Ä¢ Blue-Ocean Diagnosis
Classification: Potential Blue Ocean ‚Äî creates ‚ÄúCompliance-as-a-Stream‚Äù, but still competes with legacy maritime ERPs. Scaling the non-compliance learning loop can set a de facto market standard.

7 ‚Ä¢ Limitations & Risk Register
Physical-world events (sudden spills) not detected; requires on-site IoT integration.
Freshness gap ‚Äî relies on up-to-date regulatory bases (IMO, DPC, Navy).
Port-state acceptance ‚Äî adoption varies; mitigation via lobbying + class-society partnerships.
8 ‚Ä¢ Roadmap (T-0 ‚Üí T + 12 m)
Q	Milestone	KPI
Q0	Closed beta (3 shipowners)	< 5 % false positives
Q1	Public API + incident webhook	Integration time ‚â§ 7 days
Q2	ESG Scope-3 export module (XBRL)	‚Üë 30 % ESG-report adoption
Q3	Optimal-route ML	CO‚ÇÇ reduction ‚â• 8 %
Q4	Indexed-insurance marketplace	Premium varies by score
Executive Take: BTMaritime solves the last mile of maritime environmental due diligence with real-time hash-proof evidence and plug-and-play integration ‚Äî positioning it as baseline technology for cloud / ESG hyperscalers.

üèôÔ∏è BTUrban ‚Äì Urban Regulatory Intelligence
Use case
Predictive simulations and urban-planning reports from legal scraping ‚Äî Master Plan, LUOS, Building Code, Brazilian NBRs and heritage zones ‚Äî delivered 100 % SaaS.

1 ‚Ä¢ Stakeholder Pain Matrix
Stakeholder	Core Pain	Latent / Emergent Pain
Developer / Builder	High rework costs after project rejection	No technical + legal evidence for green-bond funding
Architect / Urbanist	Excessive time interpreting zoning	Limited view of overlapping historical norms
Licensing Authority	Overflow of manual queries	Low transparency to regulators & prosecutors
2 ‚Ä¢ Key Features (MVP v1.0)
Interactive regulatory map ‚Äî dynamic LUOS / Master Plan / heritage overlays
Simulation engine ‚Äî auto-calculates FAR, lot coverage, height in seconds
AR / VR audit visualiser ‚Äî immersive walkthrough for on-site design review
Blockchain-logged reports ‚Äî SHA-256 hash + UTC stamp, QR for city hall or registry
3 ‚Ä¢ Competitive Edge (Four Actions)
Create	Eliminate	Reduce	Raise
AR/VR visualisation + on-chain certificate	Manual zoning reviews	Viability due-diligence time	Transparency, auditability, BIM / IFC integration
4 ‚Ä¢ Compliance Coverage
Norm / Framework	Controls Met
ABNT NBR 16.280	Renovation management, engineering sign-off
ISO 19650	BIM management, CDE, versioning
WCAG 2.1	Public dashboard accessibility
ESG (GRESB)	Land-use & housing-density metrics
5 ‚Ä¢ Technical Architecture (High-Level)
Legal Scraper ‚Äî collects municipal laws, loads into Delta Lake JSON
Graph DB (Neo4j) ‚Äî models lot ‚Üí zone ‚Üí restrictions ‚Üí exceptions
Rules Engine (OPA) ‚Äî real-time index evaluation (WebAssembly)
AR/VR Renderer ‚Äî Unity WebGL, IFC/BIM & zoning textures
Certifier Service ‚Äî signs report, stores hash on Polygon, issues QR
6 ‚Ä¢ Blue-Ocean Diagnosis
Classification: Clear Blue Ocean ‚Äî turns static code analysis into immersive, auditable experience, defining ‚ÄúUrban Compliance XR‚Äù.

7 ‚Ä¢ Limitations & Risk Register
No legal advice ‚Äî final responsibility lies with a licensed professional.
Public-data dependency ‚Äî scraping fails if city hall isn‚Äôt up-to-date.
Heritage conflicts ‚Äî overlapping listings may require manual validation.
8 ‚Ä¢ Roadmap (T-0 ‚Üí T + 12 m)
Q	Milestone	KPI
Q0	Beta (2 capitals) + BIM import	Index accuracy ‚â• 95 %
Q1	BIM / IFC API + multi-user AR	Time-to-visual ‚â§ 30 s
Q2	ESG Impact module (GRESB)	‚Üë 25 % green-bond uptake
Q3	Digital-Twin module	Rework reduction ‚â• 40 %
Q4	Transfer-of-development-rights marketplace	Adjacent MRR > 15 %
Executive Take: BTUrban makes urban viability fully data-driven in XR, slashing pre-construction CAPEX and setting municipal compliance to Big-Tech standards ‚Äî a prime target for GIS and Smart-City acquirers.

üå± BTAgro ‚Äì ESG Compliance for Sustainable Agriculture
Use case
100 % digital ESG certification using the Rural Environmental Registry (CAR) and high-resolution satellite imagery ‚Äî no on-site auditor needed.

1 ‚Ä¢ Stakeholder Pain Matrix
Stakeholder	Core Pain	Latent / Emergent Pain
Farmer	Loss of premium markets without ESG seal	Reputational risk with green investors
Trader / Exporter	Embargo risk for illegal deforestation	No evidence trail for overseas buyers
ESG Manager / Investor	No auditable sustainability metrics	Hard to align portfolio to EU Taxonomy / SFDR
Certifier / Auditor	Manual, costly inspections	Low data granularity to flag greenwashing
2 ‚Ä¢ Key Features (MVP v1.0)
Automated ESG scoring ‚Äî deforestation, APP, legal reserve, water footprint via Sentinel-2 / Planet
Blockchain certificates ‚Äî SHA-256 hash + UTC stamp, QR for offline validation
Marketplace integration ‚Äî API connecting producers to carbon-credit buyers & green premiums
Change-detection alerts ‚Äî ML monitors new clearings continuously
3 ‚Ä¢ Competitive Edge (Four Actions)
Create	Eliminate	Reduce	Raise
Remote certification + credit marketplace	100 % on-site audits	Certification cost & lead-time	Transparency, granularity, audit trail
4 ‚Ä¢ Compliance Coverage
Standard / Norm	Controls Met
GRI 304 / 307	Biodiversity & Environmental Compliance
SASB Agriculture	Land-use & water management
EU Taxonomy	DNSH criteria for agriculture
ISO 14064-1	Emission quantification (Scopes 1 & 3)
Brazilian Forest Code / CAR	Arts. 29-36 (APP, RL)
5 ‚Ä¢ Technical Architecture (High-Level)
Geo-Crawler ‚Äî loads CAR shapefiles + INPE / MapBiomas layers
Imagery Pipeline ‚Äî downloads imagery, applies NDVI, NBR, AI segmentation
Scoring Engine (Python + OPA) ‚Äî computes ESG KPIs, outputs JSON-LD
Certificate Service ‚Äî signs (ECDSA), stores on Polygon, returns QR
Marketplace Connector ‚Äî REST / GraphQL to carbon exchanges & buyers
6 ‚Ä¢ Blue-Ocean Diagnosis
Classification: Potential Blue Ocean ‚Äî virtualises ESG certification and embeds credit monetisation, yet still competes with legacy validators; scaling into MRV could own a new market space.

7 ‚Ä¢ Limitations & Risk Register
No in-field validation ‚Äî accuracy depends on imagery & self-declared data; drone sampling on roadmap.
Data latency ‚Äî up to 5-day image lag; mitigation via private constellations.
Regulatory acceptance ‚Äî some buyers require hybrid audits; partnerships with tier-1 certifiers planned.
8 ‚Ä¢ Roadmap (T-0 ‚Üí T + 12 m)
Q	Milestone	KPI
Q0	Beta (50 farms) + scoring API	Deforestation accuracy ‚â• 92 %
Q1	MRV carbon integration (VERRA)	Validated credits ‚â• 10 ktCO‚ÇÇe
Q2	Water-footprint module	‚Üë 20 % EU-market uptake
Q3	Drone-on-Demand sampling	Logistics cost ‚àí 70 %
Q4	ESG Investor dashboard (SFDR)	New MRR > 18 %
Executive Take: BTAgro converts environmental compliance into tangible financial assets, unlocking green-credit revenue and slashing certification cost; the blockchain + satellite anchor creates tamper-proof evidence ‚Äî a must-have for ClimateTech M&A.

(The remaining modules ‚Äî BTEduRegTech, BTCultural, BTLexmap, BT-EHS, BTPrivacy, BTFinCompliance, BTSupplierRisk, BTAccessAudit, BTRiskLegis, BTClauseMap, BTREGULACELL, BTEnel, BTCell, BTMiner, BTHealth ‚Äî follow the same translated structure and are available upon request to avoid an excessively long single message.)

üéì BTEduRegTech ‚Äì Regulatory Automation for Education
Use case
End-to-end automation of MEC / CNE / INEP audits for program licensing, renewal and supervision, with continuous document validation and an immutable blockchain evidence trail.

1 ‚Ä¢ Stakeholder Pain Matrix
Stakeholder	Core Pain	Latent / Emergent Pain
University Holding / HEI	Rejections or costly diligences due to document gaps	Reputational loss and delayed FIES / PROUNI funding
Program Coordinator	Heavy manual effort to assemble reports and strategic plans	No real-time view of compliance gaps
INEP Auditor	Overflow of unstructured PDFs	No objective trail for evidence-based decisions
Academic Compliance	Hard to version official documents	LGPD-education non-adherence risk
2 ‚Ä¢ Key Features (MVP v1.0)
INEP audit simulator ‚Äî dynamic checklist of indicators (IDEB, CPC, CI, PDI) with instant scoring
Legal heatmaps ‚Äî traffic-light view of gaps by program, campus and modality
Documented audit trail ‚Äî SHA-256 hash + UTC stamp on every evidence, QR code for on-site committee
Smart document parser ‚Äî automatic extraction of data from curricula, agreements, diplomas (OCR + NLP)
3 ‚Ä¢ Competitive Edge (Four Actions)
Create	Eliminate	Reduce	Raise
Pre-audit simulator + legal heatmap	Manual binder assembly	Prep lead-time (90 ‚Üí 15 days)	Auditability, LGPD tracking, SIGAA / SAGU integration
4 ‚Ä¢ Compliance Coverage
Statute / Framework	Controls Met
Decree 9 235/2017	Arts. 31-55 (licensing / supervision)
MEC Ordinance 23/2017	CI / CPC / IGC quality indicators
LGPD	Arts. 6-9 (principles, lawful bases)
ISO 21001	Educational-organisation management
SOC 2 (Security, PI)	Logs, versioning, evidence integrity
5 ‚Ä¢ Technical Architecture (High-Level)
Doc Ingestor (OCR + NLP) ‚Äî normalises PDFs, Word, images to JSON-LD
Rule Engine (OPA) ‚Äî evaluates MEC / CNE rules in WebAssembly
Heatmap Service ‚Äî Redis + D3.js for real-time rendering
Certifier ‚Äî signs evidence, stores hash on Polygon, issues QR
Dashboard / API ‚Äî React (WCAG 2.1 AA) + GraphQL, CSV / XLS export
6 ‚Ä¢ Blue-Ocean Diagnosis
Classification: Innovative Red Ocean ‚Äî replaces manual processes and adds analytics, but still within the existing edu-compliance space; predictive dropout / performance analytics could open a full Blue Ocean.

7 ‚Ä¢ Limitations & Risk Register
Does not override authority decisions ‚Äî INEP committee retains autonomy.
Input-quality dependent ‚Äî outdated docs lower scoring; auto-timestamp validation on roadmap.
Sensitive data (LGPD) ‚Äî DPO workflow required; module already encrypts & tokenises PII.
8 ‚Ä¢ Roadmap (T-0 ‚Üí T + 12 m)
Q	Milestone	KPI
Q0	Pilot (2 private HEIs) + SIGAA import	Checklist accuracy ‚â• 95 %
Q1	ProUni / FIES API integration	Submission time ‚àí 70 %
Q2	CPC-forecast ML module	Approval rate + 20 %
Q3	ESG-Education dashboards (UN Global Compact)	Upsell > 15 % MRR
Q4	Power BI / Tableau plugin	BI penetration > 60 % base
Executive Take: BTEduRegTech turns academic document chaos into an auditable pipeline, surfacing non-conformities early and slashing rejection rates. Its immutable blockchain proofs set the gold standard for consolidators and edtech-focused private-equity funds.

üé≠ BTCultural ‚Äì Fiscal Compliance for Cultural Projects
Use case
End-to-end management of Brazilian cultural-incentive programs (Lei Rouanet, ANCINE), with an immutable fiscal trail, AI-driven eligibility simulation and jurisprudence risk mapping ‚Äî 100 % SaaS.

1 ‚Ä¢ Stakeholder Pain Matrix
Stakeholder	Core Pain	Latent / Emergent Pain
Cultural Producer	Expense disallowance and delayed fund release	No fiscal proof for ESG / impact reporting
Sponsor / Patron	Joint-liability risk	Lack of validated cultural ROI
Accountant / Finance	Spreadsheet sprawl & scattered invoices	Low traceability for due diligence
MinC / ANCINE Auditor	Unstandardised dossiers	Hard to detect fraud ex-ante
2 ‚Ä¢ Key Features (MVP v1.0)
Blockchain-secured archives ‚Äî every invoice, contract, receipt sealed (SHA-256 + UTC), QR-referenced
AI-assisted simulation ‚Äî NLP engine tests eligibility, spending caps, cash-flow schedule
Jurisprudence risk map ‚Äî dynamic heatmap of past disallowances by CNAE, postcode, project type
Budget-drift alerts ‚Äî real-time notifications of execution vs. approved plan
Sponsorship dashboard ‚Äî ESG panel (SDG 11, 17) for transparency to investors & government
3 ‚Ä¢ Competitive Edge (Four Actions)
Create	Eliminate	Reduce	Raise
AI simulation + on-chain archive	Isolated spreadsheets & manual NF-e control	Approval / reporting cycle	Transparency, auditability, jurisprudence-risk insight
4 ‚Ä¢ Compliance Coverage
Statute / Framework	Controls Met
Law 8 313/1991 (Rouanet)	Arts. 26-28 (tax incentives)
ANCINE Norm 124/2015	Digital reporting
IFRS / IAS 20	Government-grant disclosure
ISO 30301	Records-management evidence
SOC 2 (PI, Security)	Logs, integrity, availability
5 ‚Ä¢ Technical Architecture (High-Level)
Doc Ingestor ‚Äî captures NF-e XML, contracts, receipts; OCR on PDFs
Rules Engine (OPA) ‚Äî checks budget limits & cash-flow plan
Ledger Service ‚Äî signs (ECDSA), stores on Polygon, returns QR hash-link
Simulation Engine ‚Äî Python + Pandas ‚Äúwhat-if‚Äù spend vs. cap
Dashboard / API ‚Äî React + GraphQL; XBRL export for sponsors & MinC / ANCINE
6 ‚Ä¢ Blue-Ocean Diagnosis
Classification: Potential Blue Ocean ‚Äî replaces spreadsheets & ad-hoc consulting with real-time auditable platform; adding cultural-impact scoring and securitisation could unlock an untapped market.

7 ‚Ä¢ Limitations & Risk Register
No execution validation ‚Äî does not prove the cultural activity occurred; future IoT / streaming integration planned.
Format vs. content ‚Äî blockchain secures form & timestamp, not spending merit.
Regulatory change ‚Äî IN / ordinance updates require rule-set maintenance.
8 ‚Ä¢ Roadmap (T-0 ‚Üí T + 12 m)
Q	Milestone	KPI
Q0	MVP (5 producers) + ledger	Zero hash failure
Q1	e-SICAV & NF-e 4.0 integration	Reporting time ‚àí 60 %
Q2	ESG Impact-Score dashboard	+ 30 % corporate funding
Q3	Multi-jurisdiction (Sports Incentive Law)	New MRR > 15 %
Q4	Fraud-insurance tied to score	Loss ratio < 2 %
Executive Take: BTCultural turns cultural-tax bureaucracy into a tamper-proof evidence pipeline, attracting corporate sponsors that demand strict compliance and impact metrics ‚Äî positioning the module for consolidation into cultural-funding marketplaces and impact-fintech ecosystems.

