üìà BTQuant ‚Äì Financial Model Governance & Traceability

SaaS platform to centralize, track, and automate the lifecycle of quantitative and machine learning models in financial institutions, focusing on compliance, explainability, and drift risk mitigation.

1 ‚Ä¢ Stakeholder Pain Matrix Stakeholder Core Pain Latent / Emergent Pain Quant/Risk Teams Model/data fragmentation, lack of complete versioning Performance degradation with undetected drift Compliance/Audit Missing decision traceability and documentation Inability to explain model decisions to regulators IT/Security Manual, non-auditable processes Shadow model risks and absence of immutable logs 2 ‚Ä¢ Key Features (MVP v1.0) Centralized repository ‚Äî auditable code, data, metrics, parameters, and versions

Traceability & lineage ‚Äî interactive graph linking data ‚Üí features ‚Üí models ‚Üí decisions

Drift monitoring ‚Äî automatic alerts for performance/data distribution shifts

Integrated XAI ‚Äî SHAP, LIME, counterfactuals, and audit-ready explainability reports

Custom governance ‚Äî approval workflows with roles, permissions, and SLAs

Secure collaboration ‚Äî granular access control with workspaces and activity logs

3 ‚Ä¢ Competitive Edge (Four Actions Framework) Create Eliminate Reduce Raise End-to-end audit with XAI + lineage Fragmented repositories and manual approvals Unexplainable model risks Transparency, trust, and regulatory agility 4 ‚Ä¢ Compliance Coverage Framework/Regulation Controls Addressed Fed SR 11-7 Governance, independent validation, continuous monitoring BCBS 239 Principles 3/6/7 (completeness, accuracy, traceability) EU AI Act (2024) Articles 9-15 (registration, explainability, logging) SOC 2 Type II/ISO 27001 CC6-7 controls, security, integrity, audit trails 5 ‚Ä¢ Technical Architecture (High-Level) Model Registry API ‚Äî versions models/code/metrics with SHA-256 + UTC

Lineage Engine ‚Äî maps data ‚Üí features ‚Üí model ‚Üí decision relationships

Drift Monitor ‚Äî detects performance/distribution shifts (online/offline)

Explainability Layer ‚Äî SHAP/LIME/counterfactuals in timestamped PDF/A-4 reports

Governance & Logs ‚Äî immutable workflows/permissions (IPFS + RFC3161)

6 ‚Ä¢ Blue Ocean Diagnosis Classification: Clear Blue Ocean ‚Äî uniquely combines regulatory governance with ModelOps automation and granular traceability. No competitor offers integrated compliance + explainability + workflow management.

7 ‚Ä¢ Limitations & Risk Register Pre-deployment AIA gap ‚Äî Required for full EU AI Act compliance (planned Q1)

RFC 3161 timestamping pending ‚Äî Temporal accuracy depends on Time-Stamp Authority integration

Third-party cloud risk management ‚Äî Needed for Basel Outsourcing Framework

